<HEADLINE> Kohl to Launch Job Plan for East Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 20 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl said
today he would launch a program later this week to boost job
creation in eastern Germany.
</P>
<P>
The program will be unveiled in Berlin Thursday, Kohl said. But
no details of the plan were disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that as the result of an economic slump,
the jobless rate in eastern Germany was as high as 17.5 percent in
April, compared with 9.8 percent in western Germany and a national
average of 11.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
