<HEADLINE> Agassi Out of French Open Due To Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Andre Agassi has pulled out of the
French Open because of an injury in his right wrist, organizers
announced here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two-time French Open finalist withdrew from the German Open
in Hamburg two weeks ago citing the same injury.
</P>
<P>
The French Open, the only Grand Slam tournament Agassi has
never won, starts next Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Agassi has dropped to 28th in the latest ATP
Tour rankings and would not have been seeded in Paris, where he
reached the finals in 1990 and 1991.
</P>
<P>
He won his last Grand Slam title at the Australian Open in
1995. He also took the 1994 U.S. Open and 1992 Wimbledon titles.
</P>
<P>
Agassi's withdrawal came a day after Boris Becker pulled out of
the French Open for the fourth time since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Pete Sampras, the top-ranked player in the world, is still
uncertain after having to retire with a thigh injury in a match
Monday at the World Team Cup in Dusseldorf, Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
