<HEADLINE> Olympic Gymnastics Champion Chechi to Retire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Atlanta Olympic gymnastics gold
medalist Yuri Chechi said here on Tuesday that he will be retiring
at the end of the season.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Italian, four-time world champion, clinched the
Olympic crown in the men's rings event last summer.
</P>
<P>
Nicknamed as the "Lord of the Rings", Chechi said that out of
motivation was the main reason for his retirement.
</P>
<P>
He added that he would only compete in the Mediterranean Games
and the World University Games this year.
</P>
<P>
"Something changed in me after winning in Atlanta. Coming off
the platform, I realised I had fulfilled my task," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
