<HEADLINE> Chelsea Beats South China in Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Fresh from their 2-0 FA Cup final
triumph over Middlesbrough three days ago, the British club of
Chelsea scored a 3-2 win over Hong Kong's South China team in an
international exhibition here this evening.
</P>
<P>
Led by former Dutch star Ruud Gullit, Chelsea brought about
almost the same FA Cup final side when they met Hong Kong champion
South China today.
</P>
<P>
South China, a long-time dominant side in Hong Kong's senior
football league, had lost the chance to defend their HKFA Cup
title this year, following their loss to Sing Tao days ago.
</P>
<P>
Having set a target of less goals against and a satisfying
match to local fans, South China had been reinforced today by two
key players from local clubs Sing Tao and Golden.
</P>
<P>
But the first half proved the gap of strength between the two
sides as the visitors led South China 3-0 at the break.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea's Italian international and forward Gianluca Vialli
scored two consecutive goals within five minutes in the half.
</P>
<P>
His fellow countryman and mid-fielder Roberto di Matteo added a
goal in the closing minutes of the half.
</P>
<P>
A reshuffled South China side brought more speed into the game
as they launched more aggressive offensives in the second half. A
header by Shum Kwok Pui found the net and Cheng Siu Chung added
another goal in the dying minute of the match.  
</P>
</TEXT>
