<HEADLINE> Pakistani PM Welcomes Iran's Positive Response </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif today welcomed Iran's positive response to Pakistan's
proposal of holding a five-nation conference for peace in
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
"There is nothing better than the neighboring countries sitting
together for peace in Afghanistan," he said when replying to a
question in a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has proposed a conference of five countries including
Iran, Afghanistan, Turkmenistan and Uzbekistan to find a common
strategy for peace and stability in strife-torn Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Ambassador to Pakistan Mohammad Mehdi Akhoundzadeh said
Monday that Iran appreciates Nawaz's proposal.
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan and Iran should discourage fighting between Afghan
factions," and "both countries should try to bring them to the
negotiating table," he said.
</P>
<P>
"All efforts should be made for an early restoration of peace
and stability which are vital to the development of the region,"
said the Iranian Ambassador.  
</P>
