<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Graf Beats Hy-Boulais in Strasbourg Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Top seeded Steffi Graf rebounded from
the worst loss of her career with an easy 6-3, 6-2 victory over
Patricia Hy-Boulais Tuesday at the Strasbourg Open.
</P>
<P>
Graf beat Hy-Boulais in both previous matches but both were
three-set affairs, once in 1987 and another in 1991. It was in
Federation Cup competition at the time and Hy-Boulais was
representing Hong Kong in 1987 before gaining Canadian citizenship
and playing for the Canadian team four years later.
</P>
<P>
In other first round matches, Noako Kijimuta of Japan
eliminated eighth-seeded Bulgarian Magdalena Maleeva 7-5, 3-6,
6-1; Amelie Mauresmo of France topped Sandra Cacic of the United
States 6-2, 6-4; Dally Randriantefy of Madagascar ousted Natasha
Zvereva of Belarus 6-2, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Marjana Lucic of Croatia beat Petra Begerow of Germany 6-2,
4-6, 6-2. The 15-year-old Lucic, a qualifier, won the tournament
in Bol, Croatia last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
