<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Diplomat Expelled From Ghana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 20 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. diplomat in Ghana has been
asked to leave the country by the end of the month because his
activities "bordered on interference" in Ghana's internal
affairs.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here today quoted a foreign ministry
official as saying on Monday that Nick Robertson, director of the
U.S. Information Service in Ghana has been asked to leave by the
end of May.
</P>
<P>
The official explained that the expulsion came after Deputy
Foreign Minister Victor Gbeho complained to the U.S. ambassador
to Ghana, Edward Brynn about Robertson's activities. 
</P>
