<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, Finland Hold Annual Meeting on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia and Finland today
began a two-day annual consulatative meeting on bilateral
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued by the Ethiopian Ministry
of Economic Development and Cooperation, the objective of the
meeting is to review the progress of on-going projects and
programs assisted by the government of Finland and discuss future
areas of cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
