Cyprus, Kiev, Beirut and Damascus as well as at both ends of
Channel Tunnel.
</P>
<P>
However, analysts say that the booming Irish duty-free
industry is likely to be hit as the European Commission is
considering to eliminate duty-free sales within the European
Union by 1999. 
