<HEADLINE> First National Remote Medical Treatment Network to Be Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China's first nationwide remote
diagnosis network is expected to become operational by the end of
this month.
</P>
<P>
The Health News reported that the first group of hospitals to
be connected to the satellite network will be 20 hospitals in 10
provinces and prefectures.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the network is led by the Ministry of
Health. The network will link up with another 60 hospitals in
various provinces by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
As a developing country, more than 80 percent of China's
population live rural areas while more than 80 percent of
hospitals have been built in large or medium-sized cities.
</P>
<P>
Residents in remote areas have many difficulties in receiving
advanced medical service. Many of them have to make a long journey
to big cities to have their diseases diagnosed.
</P>
<P>
The satellite network can not only offer high-level diagnosis
of difficult and complicated cases and work out treatment plans
for patients in rural areas, it can also arrange Sino-foreign
academic exchanges for hospitals or medical colleges and
universities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
