<HEADLINE> CPPCC Tibet Regional Committee Ends Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Regional Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) of the
Tibet Autonomous Region in southwest China ended its fifth session
here today.
</P>
<P>
Pagbalha Geleg Namgyai, chairman of the CPPCC Tibet Regional
Committee, said in his closing speech that maintaining social
stability in Tibet is an important guarantee for the smooth
advancement of the reform, opening up, and modernization drive in
the region.
</P>
<P>
It is an important task of CPPCC organizations and members
across Tibet to expose and denounce the Dalai Lama's crimes of
splitting the motherland and doing harm to Tibet and to the
Tibetan Buddhism, said Pagbalha, who is also vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, China's
legislature.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that all CPPCC members in Tibet must maintain a
clear mind and take a firm and clear-cut stand in the struggle
against the Dalai's separatist activities, and should use facts
and truth to help the people immune against the deception of the
Dalai clique.
</P>
<P>
During the session, CPPCC members from all seven prefectures
and cities in Tibet discussed how to promote material, ethical,
and cultural progress for the autonomous region, and how to
enhance the democratic supervision over and involvement in
regional political and government affairs by the CPPCC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
