<HEADLINE> Sampras Out of World Team Cup Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- World number one Pete Sampras
Wednesday withdrew from the World Team Cup Tennis Championships in
Duesseldorf due to injury.
</P>
<P>
However, the American said he would play in the French Open.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who retired from his opening match against Australia's
Mark Philippoussis on Monday after straining his upper left thigh
muscle, was ruled out of the U.S. tie with Croatia. He had hoped
to play on Friday, but the doctors advised him to rest the leg.
</P>
<P>
Despite the injury, Sampras said he was confident about his
chances of winning the French title, the only grand slam to elude
him.
</P>
<P>
He played his best-ever French Open last year reaching the
semifinals before losing to eventual champion Yevgeny Kafelnikov.
Sampras leaves for the French capital on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras's clay-court campaign this season has been affected by
injuries and the World Team Cup was only his third event after
missing two tournaments with a wrist injury. 
