<HEADLINE> China, Spain Hold Trade Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Spain should seek new economic
growth areas and new breakthroughs in China's markets, and
increase its investment here, according to a senior Chinese trade
official here today.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Minister Chen Xinhua of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation told a Sino-Spanish economic and trade seminar that
cooperation between small and medium-sized enterprises of the two
countries should be promoted.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 Chinese and Spanish businesspeople attended the
seminar, which opened here today, and explored ways of how to
further increase bilateral economic and trade cooperation, and
increase investment.
</P>
<P>
At the seminar, Manuel Fernandez, secretary of state of Trade,
Tourism, and Small and Medium Businesses of the Ministry of
Economy and Finance of Spain, said that China's economic
development has opened broad prospects for bilateral cooperation
in years to come.
</P>
<P>
Spain hopes to reinforce its tourism cooperation with China,
and increase contacts between small and medium-sized companies of
the two countries, Fernandez added.
</P>
<P>
Two representatives of Spanish companies gave a briefing on
their domestic economic and trade conditions, and on relevant
preferential loan policies.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Chinese State Planning Commission and the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation also gave a
briefing on major fields during the period of the Ninth-Five-Year
Plan (1996-2000) and preferential policies on foreign funds.
</P>
</TEXT>
