<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Three policemen were killed and
33 others injured in a bus accident Tuesday night on a highway in
southern Nepal, the official RSS news agency said,
</P>
<P>
The bus overturned on the East-West Mahendra Highway at
midnight when it was heading for a major eastern Nepali town,
about 200 km from Kathmandu.
</P>
<P>
Some of the seriously injured police personnel have been
airlifted to Kathmandu by helicopter for treatment, police sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The bus driver, who fell asleep during driving causing the
accident, has been taken into custody, according to the police.
</P>
<P>
The police personnel were on a transfer trip after completing
their assignment of maintaining security for the local elections
held in West Nepal last weekend.  
