<HEADLINE> Plan Launched to Aid Minors in Need </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Youth League (CYL) of
China launched a plan here today to give a helping hand to minors
suffering special financial hardship.
</P>
<P>
The first "Heart of Love Plan to Protect Minors" aid will go to
300 children in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, and the
provinces of Shanxi, Hebei, Liaoning, Jilin, Shandong, Henan,
Guizhou, Sichuan and Shaanxi, according to an official of the CYL.
</P>
<P>
The aid recipients include handicapped children who struggle in
adverse conditions, children of displaced workers, children whose
parents who were killed in the line of duty, and minors whose
legitimate rights and interests have been infringed upon. Each
child receives 500 yuan (60.24 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The initial fund is valued at one million yuan (120,000 US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
As part of the plan, volunteers will be recruited from the
public to help the minors. An election of outstanding citizens to
protect the minors will be held late this year.
</P>
<P>
Approximately one third of the 1.2 billion Chinese are aged
under 18. China formerly promulgated the law for the protection of
minors in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
