<HEADLINE> Express Trains to HK, Macao Urged to Run Better Still </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premiers Qian Qichen
and Wu Bangguo, and State Councillor Luo Gan today met with
representatives attending a meeting in recognition of their
efforts to supply fresh and frozen foodstuff to Hong Kong and
Macao using three express trains.
</P>
<P>
Qian encouraged them to work harder and supply more of such
commodities to Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
Entrusted by Premier Li Peng, Qian, on behalf of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and the State Council,
extended his congratulations to all the participating staff who
have performed arduous, daily and significant work over the past
35 years.
</P>
<P>
The three express cargo trains have operated smoothly under the
leadership of the veteran Party and state leaders, especially with
the attention and support of late Premier Zhou Enlai, Qian
said. Many people have dedicated their youth and energy to this
work, and the ministries of foreign economic relations and trade
and railways have also done a great deal.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 35 years, he added, the three express trains have
transported countless fresh and frozen foodstuff to Hong Kong and
Macao, to meet the needs of their life, facilitating economic
prosperity and social stability there and contributing to the
return of the two regions to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
This shows that the support from China's interior areas
provides a powerful guarantee to the stability and prosperity in
Hong Kong and Macao, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Noting that there are 41 days remaining until China resumes its
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong, Qian said, adding that
after its return, efforts should be continued by departments
concerned. 
</P>
