<HEADLINE> International Ceramics Exhibition Opens in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A five-day international ceramics
exhibition opened today in Guangzhou, capital city of south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Such large-scale exhibitions have been held six times in the
Chinese cities of Guangzhou and Beijing, and the one being held is
the largest.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 ceramics machine manufacturers, ceramics
producers, and ceramics marketers from a dozen countries are
participating the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
The ceramics industry has been China's traditional industry,
and through introducing overseas funds and advanced technology
over the past decade, China has become one of the world's major
producers of civil and industrial ceramic products.
</P>
<P>
During the exhibition period, other activities including a
technological symposium, new product show, and ceramics auction
will also be held. 
