<HEADLINE> China Makes Improvement in Satellite Tracking and Controlling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Xi'an Satellite Tracking and
Control Center recently successfully positioned the newly-launched
Dongfanghong-3 communication satellite with a new tracking and
control network based on the international standard.
</P>
<P>
The Center has so far successfully tracked and controlled over
48 satellites launched by both China and other countries since it
was set up 30 years ago.
</P>
<P>
According to a local source, the Center has kept pace with the
world's advances in tracking and controlling software development,
computer simulation, satellite orbit calculation, and the accuracy
of satellite operation controls.
</P>
<P>
"Thanks to the Center's effort, China has become the third
country grasping the technology of satellite retrieval," said the
source.  
</P>
