<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Japanese Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Defense Minister Chi Haotian met
here today with a delegation from Japan's Forum on China's
Politics and Economy.
</P>
<P>
The delegation was led by Terashima Taizo, president of Japan's
Fujitsu System Integration Laboratories Ltd..
</P>
<P>
Chi, also a state councillor, said that China and Japan are
neighbors separated by a strip of water, adding that China is the
largest developing country in the world, and Japan is the largest
developed country in Asia.
</P>
<P>
"So, advancing a long-term, stable and sound relationship
between the two countries is significant to peace and
stability in Asia, and in the world as a whole," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the war of aggression against China
launched by Japanese militarists brought a catastrophe to the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
He said that "the past, if not forgotten, provides
guidance for the future."
</P>
<P>
"We hope that Japan can draw on a lesson from history and take
the road of peaceful development," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chi also expressed his appreciation for the forum's efforts to
boost bilateral friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
Terashima Taizo said that delegations from the forum have had
fruitful outcomes each time they visited China, noting that the
two countries should establish relations of mutual trust to ensure
peace and stability in east Asia.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese visitors arrived here Monday at the invitation of
the China Association for International Friendly Contact. 
</P>
