<HEADLINE> Ramos Approves Military's Takeover of Anti-Kidnap Task </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today approved the takeover by the Armed Forces of the Philippines
of the anti-kidnapping operations in Central Mindanao, the
southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ramos also ordered Southern Command Chief General
Romeo Padiernos to conduct effective actions against kidnapping
gangs in the entire Mindanao region.
</P>
<P>
Ramos issued the orders after being informed by Interior and
Local Government Secretary Robert Barbers that the spate of
kidnappings in Central Mindanao "has taken a turn for the worst".
</P>
<P>
Barbers recommended the transfer of the anti-kidnapping task
from the hands of the police who made only minimal success in the
past few years due to the lack of manpower and resources.
</P>
<P>
It was also widely believed in the country that some policemen
were kidnappers themselves or protectors of kidnappers.
</P>
<P>
The military has the manpower, resources, especially aircraft
and expertise for effective actions to address the serious
kidnapping problem in the country, Barbers said in his report.
