<HEADLINE> IAAF Ratifies World Records of Johnson and Bailey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The International Amateur Athletic
Federation Wednesday formally ratified the world records set by
Michael Johnson and Donovan Bailey at last summer's Atlanta
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
It took nearly 10 months, but the two sprinters finally got
their names in the record books.
</P>
<P>
Johnson shattered the men's 200-meter world mark with a time of
19.32 seconds while Bailey shortened the 100-meter record to 9.84
seconds.
</P>
<P>
IAAF general secretary Istvan Gyulai recently blamed the delay in
ratifying the records on problems in obtaining the proper paperwork
from the U.S. Track and Field Association.
</P>
<P>
Johnson and Bailey will meet June 1 at Toronto's SkyDome in a
150-meter match race, vying for the honor of the "World's Fastest
Man". 
</P>
</TEXT>
