<HEADLINE> Jiang Meets Hungarian National Assembly President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin said here
today that China respects the road of development chosen by the
Hungarian people and is willing to further expand co-operation
between the two countries in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said during a meeting with Gal Zoltan, president of the
National Assembly of Hungary, that such co-operation will be based
on the principle of mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit,
and mutual non-interference into each other's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Gal Zoltan, Jiang expressed the belief
that his current visit will help deepen mutual understanding and
trust, and push forward bilateral friendly cooperation
continuously.
</P>
<P>
Hungary is a country of great influence in Eastern Europe, and
in recent years, its government and people have made relentless
efforts and made remarkable achievements in safeguarding social
stability, developing its national economy, and improving its
people's living standard, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
China is glad about this and sincerely hopes that the Hungarian
people will make fresh progress in their natinal construction, he
added.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang cited China and Hungary as friendly countries
with their friendship traced back to ancient times, and reiterated
that the two countries have no basic conflicts of interests and
there are no obstacles to the further expansion of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, leaders of both countries have kept close
contact, and bilateral ties have witnessed steady growth with
cooperation continuously deepening in the political, economic and
trade, technological, and other sectors, he said.
</P>
<P>
The president noted that contact between the Chinese National
People's Congress (NPC) and the Hungarian National Assembly
constitutes an important part of bilateral ties, expressing the
hope the two organizations will further enhance their cooperation,
and play an active role in reinforcing Sino-Hungarian friendship
and improving bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Gal Zoltan said that Hungary and China have always maintained
smooth political relationship, voicing the hope the two countries
will gain relatively rapid progress in their economic and trade
coordination.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian National Assembly attaches importance to the
development of Hungary-China relations, and will continue
expanding the contacts with the Chinese NPC and its relevant
committees, Gal Zoltan said, expressing the conviction such
contact will help promote bilateral cooperation in all spheres.
</P>
</TEXT>
