<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-21 12:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Allows Foreign Wives Citizenship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait, a country with more
foreigners than locals, has up to now given nationality to a total
of 20,000 foreign women married to Kuwaiti citizens, but 30,000
more are still on the waiting list.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Interior Minister Sheikh Mohammed Al-Khaled Al-Hamed
Al-Sabah said, while replying a question at the Kuwaiti National
Assembly (Kuwaiti parliament) on Tuesday night, that up to 20,000
foreign women married to Kuwaitis were naturalized, according to
the Nationality Law.
</P>
<P>
The cases of 30,000 others were under official consideration,
added Al-Sabah.
</P>
<P>
He said the law stipulates that expatriate wives with a
specific period of marital status are entitled to have Kuwaiti
citizenship if they apply for that.
</P>
<P>
The interior minister said the law is also applicable to a
divorced or widowed foreign woman if she had child by her Kuwaiti
husband during a specific period of marriage.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Kuwaiti Nationality Law says foreign wives can
only be naturalized with a five-year-old marital state from the
date of her application for the citizenship.
</P>
<P>
Currently an estimated 40,000 foreign wives, mostly from Arab
countries and south Asian states, are yet to be granted the
Kuwaiti citizenship in the country, with a quarter of them not
even applying for the nationality.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti citizens now only make up 40 percent of the country's
158 million population with foreign nationals plus 1.25 million
expatriate workers taking up the rest . 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
