<HEADLINE> Venables Faces Legal Battle Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Australia's national football coach
Terry Venables has been taken to court by former Portsmouth
director Terry Brady.
</P>
<P>
Brady, who left the Portsmouth board last October, intended to
recover a 150,000 pound loan he made to the division one club. He
had been a director at Fratton Park for only eight months.
</P>
<P>
However, Venables, the ex-England coach and current Portsmouth
chairman, said that the money was not a loan but an investment to
buy shares. Venables bought the club in February.
</P>
<P>
The Venables-Brady case has already appeared briefly before the
Chancery Division of the High Court in London but was adjourned
for a second hearing.
</P>
<P>
Now the two sides are set for a behind-closed-doors meeting to
try and sort out the dispute over the money. 
