<HEADLINE> Main Forest Enterprises Form Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Zhonglin (China Forestry)
Industrial Development Group (ZIDG) was launched by eight major
forestry enterprises today here, in a move to introduce a modern
enterprise system.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun wrote an inscription for the birth
of the new industrial group.
</P>
<P>
The eight forestry enterprises are the China International
Forestry (Group) Corporation, China National Forestry Materials
Supply and Marketing Co., China National Forest Products Trading
Co., China National Tree Seed Co., China Forest Food and Medical
Materials Co., China Forest Import and Export Co., China
International Forest Travel Service, and the Beijing National
Timber Exchange Market.
</P>
<P>
"The group has a total assets worth 940 million yuan (118
million US dollars) and scored a turnover of 960 million yuan
(nearly 120 US dollars) in 1996," a source from the Ministry of
Forestry said.
</P>
<P>
The source added that the group has opened more than 20
domestic and international sub-branches.
</P>
<P>
According to Xu Youfang, the Minister of Forestry, China is
rich in forestry resources and the potential for this sector is
very enormous.
</P>
<P>
He said that the establishment of ZIDG will promote the
competitiveness of China's forest enterprises in the market,
especially now that more and more large foreign enterprises have
broken into China.
</P>
<P>
During the recent years the Ministry of Forestry has sped the
reform of the Ministry-attached enterprises. Last year, another
group company, the Foma (China Forestry) Machinery Group Company
was set up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
