<HEADLINE> China's Major Compact Car Maker to Issue A-Stocks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Chongqing Chang'an Automotive
Holding Company has announced plans to issue 120 million shares of
A-stock on May 23 on the Shenzhen Stock Exchanges.
</P>
<P>
They will have an issue price of 6.36 yuan. The company plans
to raise 749 million yuan for expanding its compact car production
plant and improve technical development ability.
</P>
<P>
Last year it raised 585 million yuan from B-shares in Shenzhen
on the overseas market. After this next issue, the company plans
to raise a total of 1.334 billion yuan for expanding yearly
production capacity to 150,000 Auto compact cars.
</P>
<P>
The project is estimated at a cost of 5.65 billion yuan and has
been designated as a key national automotive project of the Ninth
Five-Year Plan (1996-2000). The State Development Bank is also
committed for loans for the project.
</P>
<P>
Chang'an is China's largest compact car producer. Last year it
produced more than 70,000 compact cars, accounting for 17 percent
of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
According to the company's financial report, Chang'an had about
200 million yuan in profits over the past three years. 
</P>
