<HEADLINE> Tanzania's Hides, Skins Exports Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania earned about 2.7
million U.S. Dollars last year through exports of about 1,500
tons of raw skins and hides, compared with some 3.3 million
Dollars in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Salim Chandoo, the General Manager for the Africa Trade
Development Co. Ltd (ATD), told reporters here on Tuesday that
the price fluctuations led to decreased earnings on the products
last year.
</P>
<P>
Argentina and Brazil confined in 1995 their sales of skins and
hides in their local markets, causing a drop in the supply of the
commodity in the world market and pushing up prices, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, Brazil returned into the world market last year,
leaving prices to lower levels.
</P>
<P>
Chandoo said there was a great potential for the export of
skins and hides by Tanzania, the third largest producer in Africa
following Ethiopia and Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania's raw skins and hides usually export to Pakistan,
Hong Kong, Spain, Italy and India. Pakistan is its largest
importer. enditem


=05211130

=05252254
NNNN
19:38 19:38 g # PAB
