<HEADLINE> Zambia Resumes Cement Export to Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has resumed cement export to
Burundi in the wake of a decision made by a regional summit held in
Tanzania last month to ease sanctions against that country.
</P>
<P>
The first shipment was made some 10 days ago and currently about
500 to 700 tons of cement are exported to Burundi a week.
</P>
<P>
Zambia enjoys a 50 percent share of the cement market of Burundi
against Tanzania and Zaire, according to Patrick Gorman, Chief
Executive of Chilanga Cement Corporation, the sole cement producing
corporation in Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The nine-month sanctions on Burundi cost the corporation 20,000
US dollars in revenue.
</P>
<P>
Zambia and some other countries in the region imposed the sanctions
on July 31 last year after Burundian military leader Pierre Buyoya
took power in a military coup on July 25 from Hutu civilian President
Sylvestre Ntibantunganya.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the countries in the Great Lakes region decided to
lift the sanctions of food, medicine, agricultural and building
supplies. enditem


=05211132

=05252256
NNNN
19:40 19:40 g # PAB
</P>
