<HEADLINE> Philippine Agriculture Growth Rate Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The growth rate of the Philippines'
agriculture sector reached 4.22 percent during the first quarter
of this year, the Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
At current prices, this growth rate is translated into a gross
value of 5.44 billion US dollars, indicating an increase of 5.48
percent from last year's level, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Agriculture Secretary Salvador Escudero as
saying the growth rate is a good indicator of being able to attain
a very bullish growth rate of 4.7 percent for 1997 against last
year's growth rate of only 3.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The poultry subsector has the highest growth rate of 11.15
percent among the main subsectors, followed by the livestock
subsector with a growth rate of 6.07 percent from January to
March.
</P>
<P>
Next to the livestock is the crops subsector which attained a
3.3 percent growth. Dairy production, however, was down by 10.08
percent.
</P>
<P>
The fisheries subsector made a dramatic comeback during the
first quarter of this year with a growth rate of 0.79 percent or
8.38 percent more than last year's record, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the fishery subsector was a major loser together with
the coconut industry in terms of production performance due to the
unfavorable weather conditions and the prevalence of red tide.
</P>
</TEXT>
