<HEADLINE> Auto Import down, Export up in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China's auto imports showed a 18.77
percent decrease during the first quarter of the year, while its
exports climbed 9.95 percent, according to latest statistics from
the Ministry of the Machine-Building Industry..
</P>
<P>
Imports and exports during that period are 347 million US
dollars and 139 million dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Of the different categories, the import of whole vehicles
totaled 8,000 units worth 120 million dollars, down 48.97 percent
and 32.06 percent, respectively. China in that period imported
37,000 engines worth 26 million dollars, 15.11 percent and 35.85
percent lower than the same period last year. The import of auto
parts, components and bodies was 190 million dollars, a decrease of
3.86 percent.
</P>
<P>
Of the export auto commodities, heavy-duty trucks, cars and
special-purpose vehicles showed noticeworthy growth than the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
In the period, China exported 2,779 heavy-duty trucks, up 53.71
percent; 388 cars, a rise of 102 percent; and 158 special-purpose
vehicles, up 119 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
