<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- By affirming that "France cannot defend its interests unless
it is capable of speaking with one voice," President Jacques
Chirac Tuesday dramatized the perspective of sharing the government
with the opposition socialists.
</P>
<P>
-- One week after the incursion of the Turkish army in northern
Iraq, the signs of an escalation of the conflict is increasing, with
Syria and Iran reinforcing troops on their border with Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- By reaffirming France's role and position in the process of
European integration, President Jacques Chirac warned Tuesday
against the consequences that a change of parliamentary majority
would have upon the status of France within the European Union.
</P>
<P>
-- The French Socialist Party leader Lionel Jospin has indicated
that if his party won the legislative elections, it would
concentrate its efforts on employment by stimulating the demand on
the market. 
</P>
