<HEADLINE> Students Explore 200 Million-Year Old Mountain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 45 students at the Chinese
University of Science and Technology, who are also members of the
university's Association of Scientific Survey and Exploration,
recently concluded a four-day exploration in the Dabie Mountain,
which was formed some 226 million years ago.
</P>
<P>
They surveyed the biological resources, geological situation,
education, and economy there.
</P>
<P>
The studies of the metaphoric rocks are significant for the
studies and development of the formation of the continent and the
spread of the mineral resources in east China, according to
Chinese scientists.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, geologists from more than a dozen countries
and regions have conducted studies in the mountain and made
discoveries.
</P>
<P>
The university's Association of Scientific Survey and
Exploration has over 200 members and became a member of the China
Association of Exploration earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
The university will collaborate with the Hong Kong University
of Science and Technology this year to conduct a further survey.
</P>
