<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Modernizing Traditional Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Electronics and information
technology is contributing an increasing amount to saving
traditional industries in northeast China's Liaoning Province,
where more than 300 million yuan has been spent on computerizing
industrial production in the past several years.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 kilns and furnaces have been improved and are
providing much better results. Digital-control and digital-display
technology has been used to transform machine tools and to
increase efficiency by around 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Quality and productivity have improved a great deal as
well. Renovation of a steel rolling mill of the Anshan Iron and
Steel Corporation has brought a million yuan in profits annually.
</P>
<P>
The province, which is China's major heavy industrial base, has
also increased effort to develop hi-tech products of its own,
and has succeeded in producing 200 items, including computerized
energy-saving meters, computerized cash registers, and computers
for navigation.
</P>
<P>
The Shenyang Air-blower Plant adopted computer-aided design and
manufacturing technology in the 1980s, and shortened the design
period for its DH and CL series of turbine compressors to four
months. This alone increased its output value by more than 16
million yuan annually.  
</P>
</TEXT>
