<HEADLINE> Thailand to Sign Pact with 3 Indian Ocean Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will sign an economic
cooperation pact with Bangladesh, India and Sri Lanka next month,
according to a senior Thai Foreign Ministry official.
</P>
<P>
Kobsak Chutikul, director general of the Economic Affairs
Department was quoted today by the Thai News Agency as saying that
Thai Deputy Foreign Minister Pitak Intrawityanont will play host
to his counterparts from the three countries.
</P>
<P>
