the economic cooperation between Bangladesh, India, Sri Lanka and
Thailand will benefit these four countries and the region as a
whole, Kobsak said.
</P>
<P>
He said the grouping will approach the United Nation's Economic
and Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP) to fund
feasibility studies of proposed projects instead of the Asian
Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The ESCAP will be approached to fund studies in areas in which
all the four countries will actively pursue cooperation in trade
and investment, port facilities, facilitation of customs and
tariffs, shipping lines, fisheries and agriculture.  
