<HEADLINE> Thai Army to Wipe Out Cambodian Bandits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Thai army will implement strong
measures to wipe out Cambodian bandits who illegally entered
Thailand and robbed Thai villagers along the Thai-Cambodian
border, a Thai army official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Burapa task forces commander Major General Prawit Wongsuwan
made the remarks after his visit to the Thai-Cambodian border at
the eastern province of Sa Kaeo.
</P>
<P>
Prawit said Thai troops would not hesitate to use weapons
against Cambodian bandits.
</P>
<P>
He said during the past week, Cambodian bandits robbed Thai
villagers two times.
</P>
<P>
The Thai commander also said that the Thai army has coordinated
with the Cambodian authorities to retrieve Thai cars which were
stolen in Thailand and were sent to Cambodia.  
</P>
