<HEADLINE> Trade Fair in East China Province Fruitful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A two-day trade fair which just
ended in Nanping city in east China's Fujian province has
resulted in the inking of 113 projects which involve a total
contractual overseas investment of 185 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
These projects mainly cover the construction of hydro-power
stations, planting of high-quality grape and bamboo, and
breeding and processing of livestock and poultry.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that a large trade fair has been held in
the northern part of Fujian. The fair has attracted business
people from Japan, the United States, the Republic of Korea and
some European countries, local sources say.
</P>
<P>
The fair also yielded 75 trade contracts, from which export
volume exceeds 30 million U.S. dollars. Major export items include
textile products and deep-processed bamboo products which sell
well in 19 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Nanping, one of China's major grain producers, has one-tenth
of the country's bamboo resources.  
</P>
