<HEADLINE> China, US Join Hands to Produce Combine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, May 21 -- Jiamusi Combine Plant, China's largest
combine producer, signed a contract with John Deere Corporation of
the United States to start a harvester joint venture in northeast
China's Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The venture spent 29.9 million US dollars, of which the Chinese
side holds 40 percent of stake and US takes the rest shares. The
registered capital totaled 22.15 million dollars, with an operation
period of 50 years.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side, the Jiamusi plant, is China's largest
harvester producer, ranking among China's 500 leading industrial
enterprises. John Deere Corporation is the world's 426th largest
among the world's top 500 corporations.
</P>
<P>
The operation of the joint venture will help for the Chinese
side to improve the product quality and expand market shares at
home and abroad, a local official commented. 
