<HEADLINE> Anhui to Develop Information Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, May 21 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui province will put
stress on the electronic information industry in the 1996-2000
period.
</P>
<P>
Zhen Shitao, director of the provincial Electronic Industry
Bureau, said that Anhui plans to take the following measures in
developing the industry:
</P>
<P>
First, his bureau will allocate about 24 million US dollars in
developing information projects and helping build a special
information network for large enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Second, Anhui will use electronic information technology to
renovate traditional industries and improve the industry
structure. The electronics information industry will expand to
help with hardware-making, software-developing and other sectors.
</P>
<P>
Third, the province will expand its information services by
developing computer software application, setting up 20-25
electronics information service stations and investing 40 million
US dollars in building electronic products market in the
province. 
