<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Sword Unearthed in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A sword with bronze designs from
the Six Dynasties period (222-589) has been discovered in this
capital of east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The iron sword is 39-cm long and three-cm wide with a 16.2-cm
wooden handle and an inlaid bronze pattern in the shape of a
dragon, a traditional Chinese symbol.
</P>
<P>
The sword was unearthed at a depth of six meters at a
construction site along with a number of historical relics from
the same period.
</P>
<P>
Experts said this is the first sword of the kind to have been
found in Nanjing, and is valuable archeologically for research on
the military and metal technology.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing was the capital city of the Six Dynasties.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970521.0207 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Promote On-line Service on Campus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
