<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Police Seize 500 Kg of "Ice" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Police in south China's Guangdong
Province recently demolished nine drug factories and seized 14
suspects, more than 500 kg of "ice," and three million yuan of
money.
</P>
<P>
Earlier last December, police in Guangzhou stormed a drug
factory in Zengcheng City according to reports of citizens. They
seized five suspects and 176.3 kg of "ice," and then two more
suspects and 130.1 kg of "ice."
</P>
<P>
On April 6, another two suspects were arrested in Shenzhen. On
April 15, Xu Yongchang, the prime suspect, was arrested in
Fangchun, and 218 kg of "ice," nearly one million yuan, chemical
equipment, and vehicles were seized. Thereafter, the police seized
four other suspects, and a number of weapons.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, the suspects started to make "ice" in
partnership with a teacher at a medical college in 1992. 
