<HEADLINE> China Issues Publication Of "One Country, Two Systems" Documents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A publication containing a
selection of important documents on the "one country, two systems"
policy and on re-unification was made available today by the
Central Literature Publishing House, in major bookstores in China.
</P>
<P>
The book, in 200,000 Chinese characters, is a compilation of 57
important documents that were issued from January, 1979 to March,
1997. It was compiled by the Party Literature Research Center of
the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
They include 36 important speeches by Deng Xiaoping, Jiang
Zemin, and other senior Party and State leaders, and 19 documents
on laws and decisions adopted by the National People's Congress,
the State Council, and subcommittees. These include the Basic Law
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region and the Basic Law
of the Macao Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The book also contains documents on the Sino-British Joint
Declaration on the Hong Kong issue and the Sino-Portuguese Joint
Declaration on Macao.
</P>
<P>
The selection reflects the formation and development of Deng
Xiaoping's concept of "one country, two systems" in a systematic
way, and has the basic principles, policies, and laws formulated
by the Party and the State done in accordance with this concept.
</P>
<P>
It could be useful as a textbook for both the people and
officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
