<HEADLINE> East China County Builds Forest Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Residents in Shaxian county of east
China's Fujian province will be able to enjoy themselves in a new
forest park near the county seat.
</P>
<P>
The place was originally planned to be built into a villa
group.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, reconstruction of a highway left a piece of idle land
near the county seat. Because the place is adjacent to a hill
where the natural landscape is very beautiful, some investors
wanted to develop high-grade villas there.
</P>
<P>
"At first we agreed to the development plan, but later when
some people suggested building a forest park there, we decided to
stop building the villas", said a local official.
</P>
<P>
He said that they "prefer social and environmental benefits
because the park can serve the public."  
</P>
