<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Welcomes Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan welcomes foreign
investment in its transport sector, Transport and Communications
Minister Yuri Lavrinenko said here today.
</P>
<P>
Lavrinenko made the remarks at a new conference in the Atakent
exhibition center. He said there are broad prospects for building
a national transport network to help develop the economy.
</P>
<P>
Kazakh experts estimate that goods transportation between Asia
and Europe could yield an annual profit of 100 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
As a Central Asian country linking the two continents,
Kazakhstan should have its share of the profit and the pressing
task now is to rationalize the country's transport networks,
upgrade the existing highways and railways and set up
transport-related industries, Lavrinenko said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Kazakh government has decided to privatize
part of the railway and highway networks. 
