<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest China Province Speeding Economic Strength </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Landlocked Qinghai Province in
northwest China, on the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, has been able to
increase its economic strength by placing priority on developing
its rich natural resources.
</P>
<P>
The province has an abundance of petroleum, natural gas,
non-ferrous metals, and rare metals. It also has a potential of 21
million kilowatts of hydro-electric power, and 33.3 million
hectares of grassland and 666,000 hectares of wasteland that could
be cultivated.
</P>
<P>
So, the province has spent more than 40 billion yuan and had
8,000 projects for making use of these resources, since a local
"resource development strategy" was started in 1978, local
officials say.
</P>
<P>
The projects include the country's biggest potash fertilizer
plant, the largest asbestos production base, and the second
biggest lead and zinc mine, with a one-million-ton annual
production capacity.
</P>
<P>
An industrial system has been formed with the salt chemical and
petrochemical industries as pillars. Other industrial projects
include high-energy plants producing steel, aluminum, and
magnesium.
</P>
<P>
Because the Yangtze and Yellow rivers, the country's largest
and the second largest rivers, start in Qinghai, it has also made
an effort to tap its rich hydro-electric power resources. The
Longyangxia power station has an installed generating capacity of
1.28 million kilowatts, and a two-million-kw station, the
Lijiaxia, has just gone operational. Other smaller stations
generate a total of 6.114 billion kwh of electricity annually.
</P>
<P>
Irrigation projects in Qinghai have helped increase the amount
of irrigated farmland by 133,000 hectares and have improved
120,000 hectares of grassland, local sources say.
</P>
<P>
As a result of these efforts, the provincial GDP has gone from
1.55 billion yuan in 1978 to 18.32 in 1996, while its industrial
and agricultural output value increased from 1.96 billion yuan to
19.95 billion yuan during the same period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
