<HEADLINE> China to Set up Yellow Croaker Breeding Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian province is
preparing to build the country's biggest breeding base of large
yellow croakers - a kind of fish that makes popular seafood dish.
</P>
<P>
The province has listed aquatic products as one of its main
industry, and provincial fishery experts reported some
success in research on ways of breading yellow croaker
fingerlings through artificial insemination in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The base, covering 200 hectares, will be located in Ningde
prefecture, and consists of fish ponds and a feed production
factory.
</P>
<P>
Officials say that they plan to finish the construction within
the Ninth Five-Year-Plan (1996-2000). The first phase of the
project which started earlier this year requires an investment of
10 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The base is expected to put on the market 15 million heads of
large yellow corakers a year, generating 520 million yuan in
output value annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
