<HEADLINE> Croats to Resume "Croatian Republic of Herzeg-Bosnia" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Bosnian Croat leaders have
proposed the reestablishement of the "Croatian Republic of
Herzeg-Bosnia," a Croatia radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
The proposal was made Monday at a meeting in Croat-controlled
western Mostar following serious differences between Bosnian
Croats and Muslims on issues concerning of the Muslim-Croat
Federation, one of the two entities of the Republic of
Bosnia-Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
The commission on rebuilding "Croatian Republic of
Herzeg-Bosnia" decided to hold a meeting on Sunday in the seaside
city of Neum to officially reestablish the republic, the radio
said.
</P>
<P>
The self-proclaimed "Croatian Republic of Herzeg-Bosnia" was
officially disbanded in last August under U.S. pressure after the
Muslim-Croat Federation was founded in accordance with an
agreement both sides signed in Washington in 1994. 
</P>
