<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia promised to give five
million US dollars to the Palestinian National Authority to
support its efforts to sustain the Middle East peace process, a
Palestinian envoy said.
</P>
<P>
"We are very thankful for Indonesia's solid financial and
economic support," Dr. Assad Abdulrahman, a special envoy from the
Executive Committee of the Palestine Liberation Organization said
here last night.
