<HEADLINE> Daewoo-Backed Cement Project in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, May 21 (Xinhua) --The Daewoo Cement (Shandong) Co. Ltd,
which is being backed solely by the Daewoo Group of the Republic
of Korea (ROK), has started production in Sishui County, in
China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The project involves an investment of 300 million U.S. dollars
and has a registered capital of 99.86 million U.S. dollars. The
ROK-backed company, which is considered the most advanced
pollution-free cement producer, began production two months ahead
of schedule.
</P>
<P>
The company has its grog (fired refractory material) production
workshops in Sishui County, and its cement manufacturing workshops
and port facilities in Rizhao, on the east China coast.
</P>
<P>
Work on the company began in November of 1994. It is equipped
with the world's most advanced equipment and is expected produce
2.5 million tons of high-grade cement annually for export to ROK
and Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
An executive says that it will also build its own technology
and equipment research and development organization in the near
future.  
</P>
