<HEADLINE> Cultural Relics Found in Reservoir Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- More than 130 historical sites
have been found in the construction area of the Xiaolangdi
Reservoir in central China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The sites include tombs, tribal buildings, stone carvings,
plank roads built along cliff surface. And ancient stone ware and
pottery, dating from the Early Stone Age to the Yuan Dynasty
(1271-1368), has also been found.
</P>
<P>
Chinese archaeologists especially value those from different
periods of the Late Stone Age (10,000-4,000 years ago), of which
much stone and pottery ware has been found.
</P>
<P>
According to the experts, the find will contribute to the study
of origin of civilization along the Yellow River.  
</P>
