<HEADLINE> Canadian Company to Invest in Peruvian Mining Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, May 20 (Xinhua) -- A Canadian company will invest 1.1
billion U.S. dollars in a Peruvian mining project to help develop
the mining industry in the Latin American country.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian company, Cambior, will provide the investment in
the La Granja mining concession in the department of Cajamarca in
northern Peru.
</P>
<P>
The development of the La Granja project will provide 2,500
jobs during the construction stage and another 900 when operations
begin, according to a feasibility study.
</P>
<P>
The study said that there are 2.3 billion tons of copper
mineral reserves and an estimated 300,000 tons of fine grade
copper can be extracted from 255,000 tons of concentrated content
per year plus 45,000 tons in copper cathodes.
</P>
<P>
Sales of 600 million dollars are expected during the first two
years and 640 million dollars beginning in the third year.
</P>
