<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecological Villages Change Look of Rural Areas (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province has
been paying a great attention to environmental protection to
maintain an ecological balance, and its efforts have begun to pay
off.
</P>
<P>
Xialu Township in Shaoxing County was informed in early May
that it was given the title of "Global 500" for the year of 1996
for its outstanding achievements in ecological construction by the
United Nations Environment Program (UNEP).
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang has become famous for its successful development of
rural industry and is one of the areas in east China that has seen
the fastest growth since China decided on reform measures in the
late 1970s. This is especially true of the household
responsibility system in rural areas, and it has encouraged
surplus rural labor to work in nearby factories or find jobs in
cities.
</P>
<P>
In the past several years, the province has made environmental
protection part of its plan for local economic and social
development and has selected some rural areas to experiment with
in constructing ecological villages and towns.
</P>
<P>
Xialu Township, which is in a mountainous area, has less water
and has been an easy victim of natural adversities, which caused
serious damages to vegetation. Township authorities have made an
effort to encourage residents to plant more trees to protect the
environment, and it now has a vegetation cover of 74.2 percent,
compared with 70.03 percent in 1989.
</P>
<P>
The township government has rules and regulations banning all
pollution-causing projects in developing the local economy. One
local conglomerate spent tens of millions of yuan on shifting its
flax dyeing and finishing mill from the township seat to a tidal
zone on the coast and on installing the necessary equipment to
treat industrial waste water.
</P>
<P>
The township authorities have also taken steps to improve the
environment. The local government has implemented management
measures for the township seat and for environment and hygiene.
</P>
<P>
Local residents have been told to put their waste in bags, and
industrial and other waste is buried in centralized places. The
local government has also encouraged a comprehensive recycling of
discarded materials.
</P>
<P>
Xialu Township survived UNEP's assessment, competing with
places and projects recommended for the title of "Global 500 " for
1996. For the competition, China recommended five units but Xialu
Township survived to claim the title.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970521.0272 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecological Villages Change Look of Rural Areas (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This is a reward for the province's efforts to protect the
environment. Xialu is just one of the province's four places to
win the title of "Global 500".
</P>
<P>
The other three are Shanyi Village of Xiaoshan City, Lijia
Village of Yinxian County and Tengtou Village of Fenghua City.
</P>
<P>
The provincial environmental protection bureau says that the
province has assigned more than 100 villages or towns to
experiment with ecological construction and has successfully
established 70 ecological villages and towns, and has the largest
number of areas in China that have been given the title "Global
500" title.
</P>
<P>
Shanyi Village of Xiaoshan City has distinguished itself by
starting a number of ecological projects such as building timber
and cash forests and projects to prevent and cure plant diseases
and insect pests, and by the more rational use of resources.
</P>
<P>
The village has seen fast growth in agricultural and industrial
output value, and its per capita annual income surpasses Xiaoshan
City's.
</P>
<P>
Tengtou Village has been successful in building a
methane-generating pit with a volume of 500 cubic meters, which
has provided households with cooking gas and is offering farmers
help in cultivating aquatic products.
</P>
<P>
Village-led industries have stopped business that may cause
serious pollution and been active in environmentally-friendly
projects. Their total output value has exceeded 200 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
With its increased funds, the village has made an overall plan
to rebuild previously-scattered rural bungalows into 32 low-rise
buildings with well-designed interiors.
</P>
<P>
Provincial authorities also plan to bring the number of
ecological villages and townships to 100 by the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the State Environmental Protection Bureau say that
China has 19 projects, like the three-north afforestation belt,
and villages and townships that have won the title "Global 500"
title, which was developed by NEP to increase people's awareness
of the need for environmental protection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
