<HEADLINE> Public Network Promotes Economy In Northwest China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning, northeast China's heavy
industrial base, finds the newly opened public informtion network
very helpful in promoting the local economy.
</P>
<P>
The net, which is China's first provincial public information
network, links up the province's 13 major cities apart from being
hooked up with the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Named 'Beiguo' (meaning 'North China') Information Network, it
was designed and invested by the Dongda Software Center, one of
China's national software engineering research institutes.
</P>
<P>
It uses an optic cable for transmission and allows its users to
transmit text, graphic images, and sound simultaneously as well as
to surf the Internet or other local information nets.
</P>
<P>
The network is expected to become a major information channel
to promote the local economy, and in fact some enterprises have
already benefited from it. The Feilong Group reduced the cost of
production after learning the information on the net about where
to purchase cheaper raw materials, and the Yinzi Group concluded a
600,000-yuan steel deal through referring to the information on
the net.
</P>
<P>
Local government departments have also found the net useful in
helping them making sound judgement and decisions at work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
