<HEADLINE> Panama to Develop Capital Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Panama has the capacity to
develop a capital market as strong as its banking system, a
Panamanian official said today.
</P>
<P>
Arturo Tapia, member of the high-level commission for the
modernization of the capital markets, said that Panama can offer
Latin American and other countries a unique advantage, with its
dollarized services sector and an efficient banking system,
fundamental elements for taking the country to capital markets.
</P>
<P>
In both markets, the companies can offer their bonds directly
to the public in an effort to obtain funds, without going through
the banking system.
</P>
<P>
When a company needs financing or wants to expand its business,
it can request funds from a bank or issue bonds directly to the
public.
</P>
<P>
Tapia said that the banking systems in most developed countries
are complemented by capital markets. In the United States, the
capital market is larger than the banking system, but the banking
system in Panama is still predominant.
</P>
<P>
Since the Panamanian stock exchange initiated operations in
1990, it has had a sustained growth and registered more than 239
million dollars in trade between January and April of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
