<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Producing More Tourist Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Province, a popular
tourist destination in east China, has 58 manufacturers of tourist
products that cater to the growing tourists and hotel boom.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises can produce about 3,000 different products that
include hotel decorations and daily-use items, artwork, souvenirs,
and entertainment products.
</P>
<P>
Sales of these enterprises are expected to reach 350 million
yuan (42 million US dollars) this year, compared to 280 million
yuan in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The coastal province has the tourist trump cards as the
picturesque West Lake and Qiandao (Thousand-Island) Lake, and a
number of historical sites under state protection. It also has
over 300 hotels catering to overseas tourists, about 100 of which
are star-rated.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province generated 22.16 billion yuan in tourism
revenues, accounting for 6.4 percent of GNP and 19.9 percent
service trade.  
