<HEADLINE> Czech Trade With Germany Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The trade between the Czech Republic
and Germany dropped by 1.3 percent in the first quarter to 106.6
billion Czech koruny (about 3.68 billion U.S. dollars) compared
with the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The State Statistics Bureau said that Czech export to Germany
decreased by 0.2 percent to 53.9 billion koruny (about 1.86
billion dollars) and the import went down by 2.4 percent to 52.7
billion koruny (about 1.82 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Germany accounted for one third of the total import and export
of the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Germany's less demand for imports from the Czech Republic and
the lack of competitiveness of Czech products are believed to be
the main reasons for the trade decline between the two countries.
</P>
