<HEADLINE> China Beats England 5-0 in Opening Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion China
beat England 5-0 to take their opening group A match in top
Division 1 of the Sudirman Cup world mixed team badminton
championship here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
All-England mixed doubles titlists Liu Yong and Ge Fei, who won
all four events since their formtion earlier this year, beat Nick
Ponting and Julie Bradbury 15-7, 17-14 to pull one point down for
China.
</P>
<P>
Olympic men's singles silver medalist Dong Jiong scored an easy
15-9, 15-6 victory over Peter Knowles, now world No.75.
</P>
<P>
Reigning world champion Ye Zhaoying secured China's victory by
doing a quick work of Julia Mann 11-0, 11-2 in just ten minutes.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yong teamed up with Zhang Wei to overcome 1996 Dannish Open
runners-up and former European champion Chris Hunt and Simon
Archer 15-9, 10-15, 15-5 in the men's doubles, while Olympic
bronze medaists Qin Yiyuan and Tang Yongshu got the better of
Joanne Davies and Donna Kellogg 15-4, 15-7 in the women's doubles.
</P>
<P>
Davies usually plays with Nicola Beck, who had a leg injury
recently.
</P>
<P>
Chinese head coach Li Yongbo said: "I am overjoyed by the men's
doubles victory over the English pair. This is the first time
they won against the English pair."
</P>
<P>
"Today we played good matches but I am not totally satisfied,
especially the women's doubles and mixed doubles."
</P>
<P>
The English head coach Stephen Baddeley said he expected they
would lose 4-1.
</P>
<P>
"I am happy that we fought quite hard today. I have only a
small disappointment. We have very strong men's doubles," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said Beck would recover from the injury to compete in the
world individual championships to start next week.
</P>
<P>
England, fifth placer at last championship, will face South
Korea in the Wednesday's only group A match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
