<HEADLINE> Brazilian Coffee Exports to Hit Record High: Exporters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's overseas sales of coffee
will reach the record sum of 3.1 billion dollars this year, the
Brazilian Association of Coffee Exporters (ABECAFE) has predicted.
</P>
<P>
Due to increases in prices of coffee in international markets,
coffee export revenues for Brazil will increase 76 percent over
last year, said an ABECAFE report published today by the local
press.
</P>
<P>
Jorge Esteve, the president of that association, predicted that
the country will sell more than 16.6 million sacks of coffee (each
weighing 60 kilograms) in foreign markets, an increase of 29
percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
Esteve pointed out that coffee exports reached the
unprecedented sum of 2.6 billion dollars in 1984.
</P>
<P>
According to that association, during the first 4 months of
this year, Brazilian coffee exports totaled 5.123 billion sacks,
worth more than 862 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
