<HEADLINE> Indonesia Defeats Sweden in Group B Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia sprinted to a
good start in the Sudirman Cup world mixed team badminton
championships here on Tuesday, beating Sweden 5-0 in a group B
match in the top Division 1.
</P>
<P>
"I am satisfied with my team's performance today," said
Indonesian head coach Indra Gunawan. "Men's doubles and women's
doubles had slow starts but this is our very first match. Joko
Suprianto had just recovered from injury but today he played
fine."
</P>
<P>
World number one men's doubles pair Budiarto Sigit and Candra
Wijaya beat Peter Axelsson and Par Gunnar Jonsson 15-8, 15-10 to
give Indonesia a 1-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
Eliza and Rosiana Zelin, finalist at this March's All England
Open in Birmingham, England, defeated Marina Andrievskaya and
Catrine Bengtsson 15-8 and 17-15.
</P>
<P>
Joko Suprianto, now ranked fifth for men's singles in the
world, had to rally from one set down to beat Thomas Johansson
16-18, 15-3 and 15-9.
</P>
<P>
World number three women's singles shuttler Mia Audina defeated
Margit Borg 11-7, 11-9 while Trikus Heryanto and Minarti Timur,
ranked first in the world, took the mixed doubles against Peter
Axelsson and Catrine Bengtsson 15-9, 17-14.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's only group B match will pit Sweden against Denmark,
while England, which lost to defending champions China 5-0 on
Tuesday, will face South Korea in group A.
</P>
<P>
The top two finishers in each group in Division 1 advance to
the semi-finals for the Sudirman Cup. 
</P>
