satellite had successfully moved into the expected orbit and been
positioned at 125 degrees east longitude above the equator.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- China welcomes U.S. President Bill Clinton's announcement to
extend the most-favored-nation (MFN) trading status to China for
another year.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation said that granting the MFN status to each
other serves as the basis of maintaining the Sino-U.S. normal
economic and trade relations, when commenting on Clinton's
announcement on China's MFN status on May 19.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin, in a meeting with Foreign
Minister Yoo Chong-ha of the Republic of Korea (ROK) here
Tuesday, said that China values its ties with the ROK and is
willing to continue to develop this friendly relationship in a
long-term, stable and healthy way on the basis of the Five
Principles of Peaceful Co-existence.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- It is imperative to promote the study of philosophy and
social sciences to ensure the sound decision-making process of the
government, said State Councillor Li Tieying Tuesday at a
celebration to mark the 20th anniversary of the Chinese Academy of
Social Sciences.
</P>
<P>
-- Andrew K N Li was announced Tuesday to be recommended to
become the first chief justice in Hong Kong from July 1. If his
appointment is approved, Li will head the final court of appeal
when China resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong in
just 41 days. 
