<HEADLINE> European Shares down on Higher Interest Rates Fear </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe all
staged big losses and ended sharply lower Tuesday, depressed by a
weak Wall Street and fears of higher US interest rates.
</P>
<P>
British shares on the London market fell to session lows
towards the close on the back of sharp losses in New York and
ended down for the second day in a row, with the FTSE 100 index
finishing 37.7 points lower at 4,607.5.
</P>
