<HEADLINE> British Defense Chief Urges Bosnian Parties to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, May 20 (Xinhua) -- British new defense secretary
George Robertson on Tuesday urged Bosnia's former warring parties
to do more in consolidating peace in the country.
</P>
<P>
Robertson told a press conference here at the end of his
two-day visit to Bosnia that he had made it clear to Bosnian
politicians that the continued presence of Nato troops in Bosnia
could not be taken for granted.
</P>
<P>
