troops presence to make more efforts in implementing the Dayton
accords. In particular, he called on the parties to pass the laws
necessary for holding the international donors' conference, to
hand in war crime suspects, clear mines and reduce arms
stockpiles.
</P>
<P>
Robertson said that there is no difference between the Labor
and Conservative governments in their commitment to the Dayton
peace accords.
</P>
<P>
But he stressed that the Dayton agreement was a compromise and
to implement it also requires compromise.
</P>
<P>
The defense secretary on Monday visited Banja Luka where
Nato-led British troops were headquaterred. During the two-day
visit, he met Bosnian leaders at both state and entity levels.
</P>
