<HEADLINE> Camerounians Celebrate National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, May 20 (Xinhua) -- Camerounians today celebrated the
25th anniversary of the advent of their unified state.
</P>
<P>
The day has also been remembered and identified as a symbol of
peaceful revolution in Cameroun following a pacific transition
from the federal to the unity state.
</P>
<P>
In the nation's capital Yaounde, the celebration ceremony was
presided over by Camerounian President Paul Biya. Within two and
half hours, massive march took place at the main street the
"20 May Boulevad" which was given a face lift before the May
20 National Day.
</P>
<P>
The march began with a display of the military
aircraft and was followed by all detachments of armed forces
that were made up of the military, gendarmery, police as well as
fire brigade.
</P>
<P>
The most impressive march passes were armed vehicles, military
trucks and tankers.
</P>
<P>
Civilian march passes continued after the troops were
reviewed. Pupils and students in school uniforms holding placards
went through the main streets. The ceremony drawn a lot of
onlookers. 
</P>
